= ICMS Content Authoring =

This page covers how to create, edit, and publish email content in '''Iris Content (ICMS)'''. For information on getting access and installing the client, see [[Iris_Content_(ICMS)|Iris Content (ICMS)]].

== Content Types ==

All Iris emails should be built using the content type '''IrisEmailTemplate'''. This content type is generic enough to support any email scenario.

To create a new email template:
# Navigate to your team's folder in ICMS
# Select '''New Item'''
# Name the item descriptively (e.g., <code>MyTeam_WelcomeEmail</code>)
# Browse to '''Content Types → EmailTemplates → IrisEmailTemplate'''

=== Template Fields ===

The IrisEmailTemplate contains four fields:

{| class="wikitable"
! Field !! Purpose !! Notes
|-
| '''Subject''' || Email subject line || Supports Razor syntax for personalization
|-
| '''PlainTextBody''' || Plain text fallback || For email clients that don't render HTML
|-
| '''HtmlBodyFormat''' || HTML email body || The main visual content of the email
|-
| '''SenderProfileName''' || From address profile || Must match an onboarded sender profile
|}

=== Inline vs. Linked Content ===

Each field can be defined in two ways:

{| class="wikitable"
! Mode !! Description !! Best For
|-
| '''Inline''' || Content is defined directly in the template || Simple, single-use content
|-
| '''Linked''' || References a separate reusable content block || Localized content, shared strings
|}

Most localized content uses '''linked''' content with the content types:
* <code>IrisStringResource</code> — for short text strings
* <code>IrisTextField</code> — for longer text blocks

{{Warning|Do '''not''' use the "Targeted" option for field definitions — it does not work for email.}}

{{Warning|The HtmlBodyFormat field cannot be edited in the WYSIWYG Editor. Use the source/code editor directly. For visual HTML editing, consider the [[Email_Creatives|Email Creatives Tool]] in Iris Studio.}}

== Check Out, Check In, and Publish ==

ICMS uses a version control workflow:

{| class="wikitable"
! Action !! Effect
|-
| '''Check Out''' || Locks the item for editing (only you can modify it)
|-
| '''Check In''' || Saves your changes and unlocks the item
|-
| '''Publish''' || Makes the checked-in version live for real emails
|}

=== Key Rules ===

* Iris Studio will '''only send published content''' in live emails
* Content '''cannot be edited''' unless it is checked out
* Changes '''cannot be published''' unless the content is first checked in
* Published content '''can''' be checked out, edited, and checked in without being republished — this lets you stage updates without affecting live emails

=== Typical Workflow ===

# '''Check out''' the content item
# Make your edits (update HTML, change strings, add locale variants)
# '''Check in''' the content
# Test using the [[Email_Creatives|Email Creatives Tool]] or Iris Studio preview
# When satisfied, '''Publish''' to make changes live

{{Warning|After publishing, allow up to '''one hour''' for the Iris rendering engine cache to refresh in Production. Plan your updates accordingly.}}

== Localization ==

ICMS supports locale variants for all content fields. Each template can have multiple locale-specific versions of its content.

=== How Locales Work ===

* Each content item can have variants for different locales (e.g., <code>en-us</code>, <code>fr-fr</code>, <code>ja-jp</code>)
* At send time, Iris resolves the recipient's locale and selects the appropriate variant
* If no match is found, the default (invariant) locale is used as fallback

=== Adding Locale Variants ===

In ICMS:
# Open the content item
# Use the locale selector to add a new locale variant
# Enter the translated content for that locale
# Check in and publish when ready

=== Using the Email Creatives Tool for Localization ===

The [[Email_Creatives|Email Creatives Tool]] in Iris Studio provides a streamlined workflow:
# Build your source HTML in the '''Create''' tab
# Switch to the '''Localize''' tab
# Upload translations via CSV or XLSX file
# Export localized XML files for import back into ICMS

This is especially useful for bulk localization across many locales. See [[Email_Creatives#Localize_Tab|Email Creatives: Localize Tab]] for details.

== Assets and Images ==

Images used in emails are stored in the '''Assets''' section of ICMS:

<pre>
Site Assets → Membership.Communication → <Your Team's Folder>
</pre>

=== Image Best Practices ===

* Host all images in ICMS Assets — do not use external URLs that may be blocked by email clients
* Use absolute URLs when referencing images in HTML (ICMS provides the full URL when you upload)
* Optimize images for email — keep total email size reasonable for deliverability
* Always include <code>alt</code> text for accessibility

== Razor Syntax ==

ICMS templates support a Razor-like syntax for dynamic content:

<pre>
Hello @Model.FirstName,

Your subscription expires on @Model.ExpirationDate.
</pre>

=== Common Patterns ===

{| class="wikitable"
! Pattern !! Example !! Purpose
|-
| Simple property || <code>@Model.PropertyName</code> || Insert a dynamic value
|-
| Conditional || <code>@if(Model.IsPremium) { ... }</code> || Show/hide content based on data
|-
| Helper function || <code>@Helpers.TrackedLink(url)</code> || Click tracking for links
|}

{{Warning|Razor syntax errors will cause the email to fail at render time. Always test templates before publishing.}}

== Testing ==

Before publishing content changes, test using one of these methods:

{| class="wikitable"
! Method !! Best For
|-
| [[Email_Creatives|Email Creatives Tool]] || Visual preview of HTML, localization validation, bulk locale testing
|-
| Iris Studio Preview || End-to-end preview with real targeting data
|-
| ICP Localization and Render Tool (.exe) || Desktop tool for automated rendering and screenshot generation
|}

== Troubleshooting ==

{| class="wikitable"
! Issue !! Cause !! Resolution
|-
| Content not updating in live emails || 1-hour cache in Production || Wait for cache refresh, or test with unpublished preview
|-
| Cannot edit content || Item not checked out || Check out the item first
|-
| Cannot publish || Item not checked in || Check in your changes before publishing
|-
| Missing locale variant || Locale not added to content item || Add the locale variant in ICMS and publish
|-
| Images not displaying || External URL or broken reference || Move images to ICMS Assets and use the provided absolute URL
|}

